language: East Sumbanese, Umbu Ratu Nggai dialect
Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: Roviana borrowing - possibly avoro or gavoro; aruru = to blossom
generally speaking flower is not a very Austronesian concept
possible Javanese loan based on the semantics
used when prefixed to names of flowers
Must be possessed: e.g. 'ai funan'='tree flower', sabraka funan=citrus flower
Preceded by type of flower, or 'ai funan' (lit. 'plant flower') if unidentified or generic
